State MSM Profile: Tennessee

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Tennessee

An estimated 73,639 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Tennessee in 2013, representing 1.6% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 2,357,860 adult men of Tennessee, 3.1% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Tennessee resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (46.5%). Including both central and fringe counties, 64.5% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Tennessee, 2013

MSM in Tennessee Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Tennessee, Shelby County had the largest population of MSM at 17,466, representing 23.7% of all MSM in the state. Davidson County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Tennessee at 7.0%. This was greater than the percentage for Tennessee as a whole, which was 3.1% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Tennessee Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Nashville-DavidsonMurfreesboroFranklin Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Nashville-DavidsonMurfreesboroFranklin MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Tennessee at 28,980, or 39.4% of all MSM in the state. Of the 621,291 adult men in Nashville-DavidsonMurfreesboroFranklin, an estimated 4.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Memphis Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Memphis MSA overlaps three states: Arkansas, Mississippi and Tennessee. The Tennessee portion of the MSA had 18,540 MSM, or 25.2% of all MSM in the state and 85.4% of the 21,722 MSM in the MSA. Of 357,935 adult men in the Tennessee part of Memphis, 5.2% were MSM. This was greater than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 4.7% of adult men (21,722 out of 461,959).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Knoxville Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Knoxville MSA had a population of 6,085 MSM, or 8.3% of all MSM in Tennessee. Of the 318,846 adult men in Knoxville, an estimated 1.9% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Chattanooga Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Chattanooga MSA overlaps two states: Georgia and Tennessee. The Tennessee portion of the MSA had 3,363 MSM, or 4.6% of all MSM in the state and 81.9% of the 4,105 MSM in the MSA. Of 142,874 adult men in the Tennessee part of Chattanooga, 2.4% were MSM. This was greater than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 2.1% of adult men (4,105 out of 197,662).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Johnson City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Johnson City MSA had a population of 2,070 MSM, or 2.8% of all MSM in Tennessee. Of the 77,122 adult men in Johnson City, an estimated 2.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Kingsport-Bristol-Bristol Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Kingsport-Bristol-Bristol MSA overlaps two states: Tennessee and Virginia. The Tennessee portion of the MSA had 1,327 MSM, or 1.8% of all MSM in the state and 64.9% of the 2,046 MSM in the MSA. Of 80,923 adult men in the Tennessee part of Kingsport-Bristol-Bristol, 1.6% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.7% of adult men (2,046 out of 118,032).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Morristown Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Morristown MSA had a population of 1,110 MSM, or 1.5% of all MSM in Tennessee. Of the 42,590 adult men in Morristown, an estimated 2.6% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Jackson Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Jackson MSA had a population of 942 MSM, or 1.3% of all MSM in Tennessee. Of the 46,161 adult men in Jackson, an estimated 2.0% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Clarksville Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Clarksville MSA overlaps two states: Kentucky and Tennessee. The Tennessee portion of the MSA had 774 MSM, or 1.1% of all MSM in the state and 64.7% of the 1,196 MSM in the MSA. Of 62,746 adult men in the Tennessee part of Clarksville, 1.2% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.3% of adult men (1,196 out of 95,547).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Cleveland Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Cleveland MSA had a population of 593 MSM, or 0.8% of all MSM in Tennessee. Of the 43,360 adult men in Cleveland, an estimated 1.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
